<font color="#FF0000">INFORMATION REQUEST</font><br>
<tt>Tue Dec  3 12:05:21 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
I'd like to know what happened to the close friends I had and to trace the history of the company I served with at Ft. Benning, GA during 1959-60.  I was assigned to the 507th Detachment of the 94th Transportation Company (3rd U.S. Army), an H-34 helicopter company.<br>
Sometime during late 1960, the 507th and 94th left Ft. Benning, to be sent to what we all thought was eventually Vietnam.  We were all excited about it and I was devastated when I found that I didn't have enough time remaining on my two year draft hitch to be sent overseas.  I was assigned to a local airfield operations company to finish out my active duty commitment.<br>
After visiting the Wall, I decided to find out what happened to my buddies, but whenever I looked up units that served in Vietnam I was unable to find any reference to the 94th and 507th, so I assume they were incorporated into another unit.<br>
If anyone has info about them or can tell me where I can look them up, I'd be very grateful. Please e-mail me with anything that might help. <br>

<p><code>-- dgriffin@lightlink.com  (Dave Griffin  US 51 446 794) </code><p>


